cs.MA, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with multi-agent systems and proposes game-theoretic algorithms for control and cost allocation. 
2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper extensively uses game theory to model the behavior of agents and allocate costs. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with control of dynamic systems and proposes algorithms for optimization and game-theoretic control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication constraints and proposes algorithms for sparsity-constrained communication. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with information exchange and proposes algorithms for optimizing the trade-off between system performance and information exchange.
